i-Vietnam War movement, the antipollution and antidevelopment protests of the 1960s and 1970s, movements for local government reform and the rise of new civic groups from the mid-1970s. This rich portrayal of activists and their ideas illuminates questions of democracy, citizenship, and political participation both in contemporary Japan and in other industrialized nations more generally.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCitizenshipzJapan. 0aCivil societyzJapan. 0aPolitical activistszJapan. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  aasia scholars.  aasian studies.  acivic activism.  acivic groups.  acivic thought.  acontemporary japan.  ademocracy.  agovernment reform.  ahistorians.  aindustrialized nations.  ajapan.  ajapanese citizens.  ajapanese history.  ajapanese society.  alocal government.  amodern history.  apolitical participation.  apopular nationalism.  apostwar era.  apostwar japan.  aprotests.  aretrospective.  aself reliance.  ashimin mythology.  asocial activists.  asocial cultural history.  asocial movements.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026270640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094767240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947672423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520947672/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY